org.processmining.models.heuristics
Interface HeuristicsNet

All Known Implementing Classes:
AnnotatedHeuristicsNet, HeuristicsNetImpl, SimpleHeuristicsNet
public interface HeuristicsNet

Common interface of the HeuristicNet objects. These objects are used in algorithms like the Genetic Miner etc.

Author:
Ana Karla Alves de Medeiros

Method Detail

resetActivitiesActualFiring

void resetActivitiesActualFiring()
Resets the variable that keeps track of activities that are actually fired during the parsing of a log. The activities that do not fire are not shown in the graphical representation of the HeuristicsNet.
In this case, all activities have their counters set to 0.

resetArcUsage

void resetArcUsage()
Resets the variable that keeps track of how often arcs are actually used during the parsing of a log by this HeuristicsNet.
In this case, all arc usages are set to 0.

getActivitiesActualFiring

int[] getActivitiesActualFiring()
Retrieves the variable that keeps track of how often activities have been executed (or fired) during the parsing of a log.

Returns:
An array containing the number of times that a given activity has fired.

getArcUsage

cern.colt.matrix.DoubleMatrix2D getArcUsage()

Returns:
A matrix containing the number of times that a given arc has been used.

setActivitiesActualFiring

boolean setActivitiesActualFiring(int[] newActivitiesActualFiring)
Sets the variable that keeps track of how often activities have been executed during the parsing of a log by this HeuristicsNet.

Parameters:
newActivitiesActualFiring - array containing the new values for the activities firing. This variable should have the same length of the current variable used to keep track of the activities firing.
Returns:
true if the variable has been successfully updated, false otherwise.

setArcUsage

boolean setArcUsage(cern.colt.matrix.DoubleMatrix2D newArcUsage)
Sets the variable that keeps track of how often arcs are actually used during the parsing of a log by this HeuristicsNet.

Parameters:
newArcUsage - matrix containing the new arc usage values for the activities. This variable should have the same dimension that the current matrix has.
Returns:
true if the variable has been successfully updated, false otherwise.

increaseArcUsage

void increaseArcUsage(int activity,
                      HNSubSet usedInputActivities,
                      int amount)
Increases arc usage in this HeuristicsNet object.

Parameters:
activity - index of the activity to which output arcs should be increased.
usedInputActivities - HNSubSet with the activities to which these output arcs connect to. In other words, set containing the output activities.
amount - value by which each output arc usage should be increased.

compareTo

int compareTo(HeuristicsNet otherHeuristicsNet)
Compares other HeuristicsNet object with this HeuristicsNet object. The comparison is based on their fitness values.

Parameters:
otherHeuristicsNet - other HeuristicsNet object to compare with this HeuristicsNet object.
Returns:
0 if the two HeuristicsNets have the same fitness value, 1 if this object's fitness value is bigger than the fitness value of the other object, -1 if the this object's fitness value is smaller than the other object's fitness value.

equals

boolean equals(java.lang.Object other)
Checks if a given HeuristicsNet object is equal to this HeuristicsNet object. Two HeuristicsNet objects are equal when: (i) they have the same size; (ii) they contain the same ActivitiesMappingStructures; and (iii) their input and output sets are the same.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Parameters:
other - HeuristicsNet object to compare with this one.
Returns:
true if the two HeuristicsNet objects satisfy the three conditions above, false otherwise.

disconnectArcsUsedBelowThreshold

void disconnectArcsUsedBelowThreshold(double threshold)
Removes from this HeuristicsNet object all the arcs that have not been used up to a given threshold.

Parameters:
threshold - double value of the threshold to be used during the arc pruning.

disconnectUnusedElements

void disconnectUnusedElements()
Disconnects in this HeuristicsNet object the activities and arcs that are not used during the parsing of an event log.

Note: This method should be used with care since, at the starting of a parsing, no elements (activities or arcs) have been used!
